reviews_data.review_text: There was a lil boy who checked me out and he was the best worker I’ve seen in years. Quick to greet, and answer my question about sugar free flavors. He had such a nice and professional tone. He got my coffee to me in what felt like less than a minute and by the time he gave it to me he had already let me know where the creamer was. Loved how quickly and efficiently I got my delicious coffee. I ordered a regular hot brew coffee with sugar free caramel and then added creamer. It was perfect. Usually I prefer my nice organic coffee at the house but this was better! Worth every penny for quality ingredients.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thanks so much for the great review Sabrina, I am so pleased to hear you had such a lovely time with us enjoying your coffee! 
Please come and see us again soon 


Becky Howden
Manager

reviews_data.review_text: Stopped in for coffee and the drinks were so watered down that there was no flavor of coffee. Asked for a remake that actually tasted like coffee and they stated that they would have to charge me for another shot of espresso. Did not remake drinks.

reviews_data.review_text: I happened to come across this hidden delightful little place late one night by chance, I was in attendance at a convention Nextdoor at the Charles Mack a nice place also but the gentleman my husband’s 106 going on 107 year old uncle was cold so I knew he loved coffee and went in search of some, the nice staff lady said when I told her what I was looking for said it’s right next door how very convenient, I went by outside and the allure of coffee beans drew me up the stairs and in the the doors, there was a well dressed lady waiting on a young man and a couple sitting relaxed in chairs drinking coffee and playing a game provided there. I looked around very clean and very well maintained  business, the wonderful smells of coffees taunting your nostrils as you wait to order, the place had seating arranged and decor to accommodate the small building space, making it quaint, the lady behind the counter was finished and took my order I got a bag of a chocolate cherry coffee my eyes had found in the waiting , I ordered two coffees, and I told her the hot one was for a hundred and six year old next door, we had a pleasant conversation. I took the man his coffee and he smiled really big , he took a sip and said “ this is some pretty good coffee “ with a big grin!! If you have not tried this little tasty place Carl said you need too! 🥰🥰  it warmed him up and tasted great too!
reviews_data.owner_answer: My dearest Amy it was a pleasure to have served coffee to you folks and we are so very happy you found us and had such a wonderful experience!

reviews_data.review_text:
Summit Coffee in Mooresville is my favorite coffee shop! Becky (the manager) & her team are always so warm & friendly when you come in, whether you're doing a walk-up order or placing an order on the app. The atmosphere is so bright & cozy, too!
I love that Summit has rotating seasonal coffee drinks. I always enjoy seeing the new offerings pop up, but of course, I get stuck on ONE favorite. And this location is really the only one nearby that has avocado toast. I don't know how Becky makes it, but it tastes amazing! And it's ALWAYS so nicely presented...picture-worthy! I love that they cut the slice in half, which makes it easier to eat on the go. I admit, I eat it in the car as soon as possible. :D My coffee always comes out perfect - whether hot or iced.

Kudos to Summit Coffee - Mooresville!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Angela! thats so sweet of you to say! I will pass on your kind words to the team! Hope to see you soon for that Blueberry Latte & Avo toast

reviews_data.review_text: Very attractive coffee shop and pleasant atmosphere.

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee and friendly service. I love the seasonal menus!

reviews_data.review_text: I’m in town for a sports cards show and stopped in to get some coffee. The shop is so cute, great atmosphere, great customer service and the best coffee drinks!! My husband isn’t a big coffee drinker and he LOVED the iced pumpkin coffee drink I got him!  I’d this were in my town, I’d forget all about Starbucks 😆🤩
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thats so sweet of you guys thanks so much! glad you liked our baked goods and I agree the Pumpkin Latte is a thing of beauty :)

reviews_data.review_text: I’m a regular. I love it here! Becky, the manager, is super sweet and sociable. All the baristas make great coffee!! Honestly, sometimes I go more so to socialize with them 😂😂. The customer service is great, and the shop is cute and clean.

reviews_data.review_text:
Such a cozy place to drink some delicious coffee and tea. A great place to meet and just hangout. They have free WiFi for you to conduct some business using your laptop.

The place is nicely lit, with a great color scheme. The relaxing music will also place you in a relaxed mood.

The coffee and tea are delicious you will keep drinking all day long. I love the mugs. And the gold spoons are so unique. Very inspirational.

Staff are very friendly and they make you feel like family.

reviews_data.review_text: There is one girl that works there with curly hair and she is awesome. But the young girl tonight turned the lights off on me. I didn't realize they closed at 5pm. It was socially awkward and immature. Please train your staff to have adult communication skills. They have to use their words to be successful in life. She could have said "mam, I am so sorry but we are closing in 10 minutes". I would have said, " I'm so sorry I didn't realize. Thank you for letting me know." Nope just lights off and loudly slammed pots and pans. Good lord.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Jennifer, my name is Lauren, and I'm the (curly haired) manager. This is shocking and I am so genuinely sorry that this happened. If you're up for it, could you please shoot me an email to mooresville@summitcoffee.com so we can chat? I'd really like to make this right for you.

I'd like to add, after looking at your profile pic, I always look forward to seeing you and your daughter walk in the door for her regular hot chocolate! Always makes my day :)

reviews_data.review_text: Summit is my favorite local coffee and I was and am thrilled that they now have a location in Mooresville! I love the atmosphere and style, always being greeted by the friendly staff, and of course the delicious coffee (and other coffee free beverages) and snacks available.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Kathryn! We always love to see your pics on Instagram :) See you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place and the coffee!
reviews_data.owner_answer: So happy to have you!! Thanks Taylor!

reviews_data.review_text: Summit Coffee in general pretty bad at having sufficient supply. This location is probably one of the worst I’ve been to. Staff is clueless
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Arif, we're so sorry you had a poor experience with us. After speaking with my baristas, I wanted to address your concerns--we only carry around 4-5 different drip coffees for retail at a time, and we never carry 5lb bags for retail. However, all of our coffee options & sizes are available on the Summit website to order! Thanks for the honest feedback, we hope to see you again in the future.

reviews_data.review_text: Incredibly friendly staff and delicious coffee and beer selections!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jessica, thanks so much for the great review! We always strive to make people feel welcome and at-home in the cafe. Hope to see you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The espresso was pretty sour. I don’t think the automatic machine they use to pull the espresso does the beans justice. I made home espresso with beans from summit coffee and it was pretty good but the machine they used in house made the espresso taste under extracted/sour. Maybe it just needed to be recalibrated or something but the cappuccino I got was not very enjoyable. The chai latte I got was delicious though.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the review, Matthew. My apologies for your espresso experience. The extraction time is checked every morning and sampled by a barista before serving to customers. Even given our efforts, I understand there is a possibility that the extraction wasn't proper for your cappuccino. We will continue to strive for perfection in our products. Our baristas are experienced and compulsive about their craft. Your comments will be taken to heart, and we thank you for the chance to improve. Hopefully you will continue to be a part of our family at the cafe and give us another chance to make a perfect cappuccino for you.

reviews_data.review_text: Such a cozy and cute coffee shop. My latte and bagel were delicious! 10/10 recommend!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jordyn thanks so much for your kind review!

I love coming here!! Everyone is so friendly and I love their caramel lattes. The manager, Lauren, is so nice and helpful every time I come in. Also appreciate that they don’t upcharge for alternative milk!
Best thing to happen in Downtown Mooresville. Congrats !! 🏔 ☕️ 🎈
Great new space. Plenty of outlets and good beverages.

Man, just an awesome experience. The team is extremely welcoming, design is super cool, music str8 🔥, and all the drinks/coffee are hot and fabulous. Best matcha latte in the history of the universe. Will be a regular fo lyfe ❤️☕️
reviews_data.owner_answer: Yay thanks Matthew thats great to hear! thanks for the wonderful review

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for your comment Willow. Our baristas take an artistic pride in their drink preparations, and the scones are always fresh and moist. Glad you enjoyed. Come again!

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind review and photos. We strive to create a friendly setting for friends and family. Nice to hear about your positive experience. hope to see you again soon!

I love that Summit has rotating seasonal coffee drinks. I always enjoy seeing the new offerings pop up, but of course, I get stuck on ONE favorite. And this location is really the only one nearby that has avocado toast. I don't know how Becky makes it, but it tastes amazing! And it's ALWAYS so nicely presented...picture-worthy! I love that they cut the slice in half, which makes it easier to eat on the go. I admit, I eat it in the car as soon as possible. :D My coffee always comes out perfect - whether hot or iced.

Kudos to Summit Coffee - Mooresville!
